canonical:
  title: 上元靑詞
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 道固宅於希夷迎隨不見神若存於怳惚禍福無常念眇眇之資臨元元之衆克艱王業居多夕惕之心寅奉天威恒有日臨之畏况屬群仙之校錄宜邀上帝之保持恭按眞科式嚴淨醮仰兾冥然之聽優加惠我之私擁茨福之方將永于多享保蘿圖於可久展也大成
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 上元靑詞
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 道固宅於希夷。迎隨不見。神若存於怳惚。禍福無常。念眇眇之資。臨元元之衆。克艱王業。居多夕惕之心。寅奉天威。恒有日臨之畏。况屬群仙之校錄。宜邀上帝之保持。恭按眞科。式嚴淨醮。仰兾冥然之聽。優加惠我之私。擁茨福之方將。永于多享。保蘿圖於可久。展也大成。
korean:
  title: 상원청사
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 도(道)는 본래 오묘한 본체(本體)에 존재하여 맞이하거나 따라가도 보이지 아니하는 것이요, 신(神)은 뚜렷이 보이지 않는 황홀한 가운데 있는 듯하여, 화란과 복을 내려 주심이 무상(無常)합니다. 작은 자질을 가지고 나라의 근원이 되는 대중에게 임하는 것을 생각하면, 왕업(王業)이 매우 어려워 저녁에도 조심하는 마음으로 있음이 많으며, 공경하여 하늘의 위엄을 받드오니, 항상 태양이 위에서 내려다보는 두려움이 있사옵니다. 더욱이 여러 신선의 교록(校錄)에 속하오니, 상제(上帝)의 보호하고 도와주심을 맞이하는 것이 옳겠으므로, 엄숙히 법을 살펴 깨끗한 제사를 지내옵니다. 아득한 상제께서 들으시고, 나에게 은혜 주시는 사사로움을 더하시어 이엉풀같은 복이 금방 오도록 옹호하시되 오래도록 많이 누리게 하시고, 국토를 오래도록 보호하시어 크게 성취하게 하여 주시옵기 우러러 비옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1180_010_0060&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Blue Prayer for the Lantern Festival
  author: Lee Gyeou-bo
  language: eng
  text: The Way dwells in subtle mystery—sought, yet never seen; followed, yet never grasped. The Divine moves through twilight and shadow, neither clear nor absent, bestowing fortune and calamity in turns without pattern. I, bearing meager gifts, stand before the multitude that forms the realm's foundation. How arduous is kingship—my heart knows only evening watchfulness and constant care. With reverence I uphold Heaven's majesty, forever trembling beneath the gaze of the celestial eye. Yet more—I am inscribed in the registers of the immortal spirits; therefore it is fitting to seek the protection and blessing of the Supreme Ruler. With solemn observance of sacred law, I perform this pure ritual. In that distant realm where the Supreme Ruler listens, may He hear these words and deign to extend His grace upon me. Let the humble grasses of fortune flourish and endure, that I may enjoy their abundance for long years. Guard the realm in perpetuity, that all may reach toward great and lasting fulfillment. This is my humble and sincere prayer.
  footnotes:
    - This is a formal prayer (青詞) composed for the Upper Lantern Festival (上元), the fifteenth day of the first lunar month, an important Daoist observance.
    - 李奎報 (1168-1241) was a renowned Goryeo scholar-official and writer, known for his mastery of both Confucian and Daoist traditions.
    - The prayer employs classical Daoist cosmological language—the Way (道), the Divine (神), and the Supreme Ruler (上帝)—reflecting the spiritual syncretism of medieval East Asian thought.
